title: Push-Ups
instructions: Get down on all fours, placing your hands slightly wider than your shoulders.
Straighten your arms and legs.
Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor.
Pause, then push yourself back up.
Repeat.

title: Pull-Ups
instructions: Grab The Bar. Grip it about shoulder-width apart. ...
Hang. Raise your feet off the floor by bending your knees. ...
Pull. Pull yourself up by pulling your elbows down to the floor. ...
Pass The bar. ...
Repeat.

title: Squats
instructions: Stand straight with feet hip-width apart. ...
Tighten your stomach muscles. ...
Lower down, as if sitting in an invisible chair. ...
Straighten your legs to lift back up. ...
Repeat the movement.

title: Burpees
instructions: Get down on all fours, placing your hands slightly wider than your shoulders.
Straighten your arms and legs.
Lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor.
Push up and jump your feet to your hands and spring upwards raising your hands in the air.
Land back down, place your hand by your feet and jump your feet back into push up position.
Repeat.

title: Sit-Ups
instructions: Lie on your back with a slight bend in your knees and arms bent at the elbows and hands lightly touching your head by the ears.
Engage your core and lift your upper body so your elbows touch your knees.
Return to the start position
Repeat.

title: Lunges
instructions: Start by standing straight.
Step forward with one foot until your leg reaches a 90-degree angle.
Lift your front lunging leg to return to the starting position.
Repeat.

title: V-sit ups
instructions: Lie flat on your back. Extend your arms overhead, hands touching the floor.
Squeeze your abs and lift your shoulders and legs off the floor at the same time. Try to reach your hands to your feet. in the middle of your body
Slowly return back to starting position.
Repeat.

title: Crunches
instructions: Lie on your back on a mat with knees bent and feet flat on the floor.
Cross your arms in front of your chest.
Crunch your ab muscles to lift your shoulders and feet off the mat.
Hold for a second, then slowly come back down to starting position.
Repeat.

title: Pendulum
instructions: lay on your back, keeping your legs together and knees straight, raise your legs until they're perpendicular with the floor.
Contract your abs and slowly lower your legs to the right, stopping just before your feet touch the floor.
then reverse the movement and repeat on the other side.
Repeat.

title: Reverse fly
instructions: Start standing with your feet hip-width apart. Holding a dumbbell in each arm, bring your arms straight out in front of you.
Slowly spread your arms apart to a T-shape. Move slowly and with control.
With control, bring your arms back to the parallel position.
Repeat.

title: Shoulder Press
instructions: Stand with feet shoulder-width apart and hold the dumbbells at shoulder height with your elbows at a 90-degree angle.
Slowly lift the dumbbells above your head without fully straightening your arms. Pause at the top.
Repeat.

title: Side raises
instructions: Stand or sit with a dumbbell in each hand at your sides.
Keep your back straight, brace your core, and then slowly lift the weights out to the side until your arms are parallel with the floor.
elbow slightly bent.
Repeat.

title: Mountain Climbers
instructions: Get down on all fours, placing your hands slightly wider than your shoulders.
Straighten your arms and legs.
Bring one knee towards your abs and then straighten it back out and do the same with the other leg.
Repeat.

title: Tuck Jumps
instructions: Standing with your feet a little less than shoulder-width apart.
Drop down a little into a quarter squat then explode into the air.
Keep your back straight throughout, and tuck your knees up towards your chest as much as possible, before landing as softly as you can.
Repeat.

title: Floor to Stands
instructions: Lay down on your front.
Push up into all fours and get into a standing position
Pause and then get back into a laying down position.
Repeat.
